Usage: run_vsr [-help] [-log_file <string>] [-no_taper_to_pinwidth]
               [-post_load_script <string>] [-pre_load_script <string>]
               [-remove_existing_route]
               [-route_type_order {bus diffPair match nets shield}]
               [-run_VSR_Script <string>] [-share_shields] [-sel_net <string> | -incl_net_type {bus diffPair match nets shield} | -nets_file <string>]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
-incl_net_type {bus diffPair match nets shield}
                           # List of net types for VSR router to route. (enum_list, optional)
-log_file <string>         # FileName for routing report (string, optional)
-nets_file <string>        # FileName for nets to be routed (string, optional)
-no_taper_to_pinwidth      # Used to switchoff the default taper pin width
                           # feature (bool, optional)
-post_load_script <string> # Script to be executed by VSR after loading the
                           # design (string, optional)
-pre_load_script <string>  # Script to be executed by VSR before loading the
                           # design (string, optional)
-remove_existing_route     # All selected nets (fixed, normal), including
                           # shield, excluding power nets, will be deleted
                           # before the route (bool, optional)
-route_type_order {bus diffPair match nets shield}
                           # List of valid constraint type in the preferred
                           # routing order (enum_list, optional)
-run_VSR_Script <string>   # User defined script to be executed by VSR
                           # (string, optional)
-sel_net <string>          # List of selected net names (string, optional)
-share_shields             # Used to enable the sharing of shields
                           # (bool, optional)